messages.message: On prod, it doesnt show whats in these tables however indicates they have rows
was this in Build? what was the prompt you used?
often, if you use a prompt like “extract all text” or “extract all tables”, you’ll run into the limitations of the context window, so the returned value can be cut off
are these 3 tables all part of 1 big table? if not, have you tried extracting these tables individually?
i thought were were suppose to do extract all tables then use clean to refine it?
no, we do not recommend extracting all tables because of the context window issue - did you see some documentation that said otherwise?
I thought that was in the demo that @lydia gave in the all hands
I don't think context window is an issue if you have object detection enabled, since "Extract all tables" in Reasoning mode is running the table pipeline
@joshbronko just to confirm, you have object detection enabled, right?

if you hover over the light bulb next to the document name, do you see any table entities extracted? The tables should be highlighted on the document - do you see them?

Also, did you happen to move this project across workspaces?
I’m afk for a bit but will check. Pretty sure object was enabled. It was a brand new project
